                <div>
                    <head>6. Verse</head>
                    <list>
                        <item><gi>rhyme</gi> element added to make rhyming part of
                            metrical line</item>
                        <item>Core: <gi>lg</gi> (line-groups) enclose <gi>l</gi> (line)
                            elements</item>
                        <item>Elements defined: <gi>caesura</gi>, <gi>metDecl</gi>,
                                <gi>metSym</gi>, <gi>rhyme</gi></item>
                    </list>

                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="tiny">
            <lg rhyme="abab">
                <l>What passing-bells for these who die as <rhyme label="a">cattle</rhyme>?</l>
                <l>Only the monstrous anger of the <rhyme label="b">guns</rhyme>.</l>
                <l>Only the stuttering rifles' rapid <rhyme label="a">rattle</rhyme></l>
                <l>Can patter out their hasty <rhyme label="b">orisons</rhyme>. </l>
            </lg>
          </egXML>
                </div>

